  "text": "Gibberellins: Gibberellins are considered as plant hormones ensuring the lengthening of the stems and the expansion of the leaves. Some types of dwarfism have been attributed to gibberellin deficiency, but this has no effect on the roots. Many plant growth promoting bacteria are reported to produce gibberellins [CITATION_1] , including Rhizobium and S. meliloti [CITATION_2] .",
